{"id": "EUVD-2023-59863", "enisaUuid": "3f0590ba-5fb3-3d01-8009-4ffe96ecdd24", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nbpf: Fix memleak due to fentry attach failure\n\nIf it fails to attach fentry, the allocated bpf trampoline image will be\nleft in the system. That can be verified by checking /proc/kallsyms.\n\nThis meamleak can be verified by a simple bpf program as follows:\n\n  SEC(\"fentry/trap_init\")\n  int fentry_run()\n  {\n      return 0;\n  }\n\nIt will fail to attach trap_init because this function is freed after\nkernel init, and then we can find the trampoline image is left in the\nsystem by checking /proc/kallsyms.\n\n  $ tail /proc/kallsyms\n  ffffffffc0613000 t bpf_trampoline_6442453466_1  [bpf]\n  ffffffffc06c3000 t bpf_trampoline_6442453466_1  [bpf]\n\n  $ bpftool btf dump file /sys/kernel/btf/vmlinux | grep \"FUNC 'trap_init'\"\n  [2522] FUNC 'trap_init' type_id=119 linkage=static\n\n  $ echo $((6442453466 & 0x7fffffff))\n  2522\n\nNote that there are two left bpf trampoline images, that is because the\nlibbpf will fallback to raw tracepoint if -EINVAL is returned.", "datePublished": "2025-09-15T15:31:28", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-03T15:30:27", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/20109ddd5bea2c24d790debf5d02584ef24c3f5e", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/f72c67d1a82dada7d6d504c806e111e913721a30", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/6aa27775db63ba8c7c73891c7dfb71ddc230c48d", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/108598c39eefbedc9882273ac0df96127a629220", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2023-53221"], "aliases": ["CVE-2023-53221"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0db60776-0d69-3267-9f09-71ca736b5134", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "18df75a8-518e-3d55-852d-7ea95badce59", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.4.4"}, {"id": "20022de3-c120-3f8b-aa78-ee661e37dc8b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "e21d2b92354b3cd25dd774ebb0f0e52ff04a7861"}, {"id": "31d244ba-7921-36cf-b0c1-86836dd53f0f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.1.39"}, {"id": "4e5e2e6d-9dcb-37d2-93fc-22605c61312e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "e21aa341785c679dd409c8cb71f864c00fe6c463 <6aa27775db63ba8c7c73891c7dfb71ddc230c48d"}, {"id": "5b441b41-ba8b-3154-85d8-12175fa0c237", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "85d177f56e5256e14b74a65940f981f6e3e8bb32"}, {"id": "5e8150ef-cdfa-3114-bc64-9069284571e2", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "e21aa341785c679dd409c8cb71f864c00fe6c463 <108598c39eefbedc9882273ac0df96127a629220"}, {"id": "68ece43f-3e37-373e-9f3b-fdf80cd66ad6", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.3.13"}, {"id": "79e8754f-09c7-39a1-89e3-acec200ae44c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.12"}, {"id": "b4735a6c-5ed9-344c-84b7-34614bd7fc26", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.5"}, {"id": "b544b54e-75e8-3470-a11d-b045dcba82c3", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "e21aa341785c679dd409c8cb71f864c00fe6c463 <f72c67d1a82dada7d6d504c806e111e913721a30"}, {"id": "d2db425f-ca50-3d67-a6ac-d7382dea1013", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "e21aa341785c679dd409c8cb71f864c00fe6c463 <20109ddd5bea2c24d790debf5d02584ef24c3f5e"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "57646d24-cc7b-3e8f-8d42-22de3a84470a", "vendor": {"name": "Linux"}}], "isExploited": false}